{
  "stem": "23090.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was like, during the day after like, maybe a meal or something.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But sickness goes 24 hours.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And your body and your system doesn't know from time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we lost-- every day we lost hundreds and hundreds of people would just rotate out of these barracks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that is, that is the most, to me, that is the most terrible time that I can remember it being in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, I smelled the flesh.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, that was not, not the thing, although I didn't know it was flesh at the time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But the crematoriums were right, like, if I was-- my barrack was here, crematorium would be at the end of this driveway, which is maybe 150 feet.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the smoke, and the flesh, this burning of the flesh, was just common.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was like a daily occurrence, around the clock.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Death was just everywhere, everywhere.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You, you were no longer with the Germans themselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You were now under the guidance of kapos, of, of, of kapos that were brought in from the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Mostly, I remember were Ukraines.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I'm not trying to put a tag on Ukraines as a whole, but for some unknown reason, the Germans-- well, they volunteered or-- how-- in whatever capacity, they stood out to me in Auschwitz as the culprits, or at least, they were in the ovens with the Jewish assistants-- with the-- they had the Jews that they delegated also, or they assigned, or they made you go-- to carry the bodies and so on.",
      "word_count": 74
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We had body details.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They had all kinds of details there to, to accommodate the, the final solution, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
